unpause().details: Unpauses the smart contract. Can only be called by the CEO, since  one reason we may pause the contract is when CFO or COO accounts are  compromised.

listings.details: stores all of the submitted Listings

listingsArray.details: Also store listings hash as an array in order to loop over later during upkeep

devdoc.title: Listings manages buying and selling of listed items

performUpkeep(bytes).notice: method that is actually executed by the keepers, via the registry. The data returned by the checkUpkeep simulation will be passed into this method to actually be executed.

unpause().notice: This is public rather than external so it can be called by  derived contracts.
